FBIS3-25506 "drafr035_d_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola Clashes Between UNITA, Government Forces Continues Twelve FAPLA Soldiers Killed MB2202093394 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in Portuguese 0600 GMT 22 Feb 94 MB2202093394 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] The war situation prevails in Lunda Sul Province, with government troops on the offensive. This was revealed yesterday by the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola [FALA] North West Command. The source said that over the weekend the Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party [MPLA-PT] troops attacked the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] in Caiaza area, on Saurimo-Ndala and Lucapa-Saurimo roads. There were also clashes in the Mona Quimbundo area, where the People's Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola [FAPLA] abducted some peasants in the villages. The North West command has described these operations as coward provocations to which FALA responded promptly, killing 12 FAPLA soldiers.
